approach :- 

i/p :- 4 3 2 7 4 3 1

1. sbse phele piche se check krenege ki element i+1 > i to us i indexko ek variable 'p' m store krenge
    (kyoki yadi element i+1 < i aur hum swap krne ke liye i ko lenge to after swapping value chote milegi)
    Ex :- 1 3 2 => {after swap (3, 2)} -> 1 2 3

2. ab array ke last se us p index tk p-index-element se just bdi value find krenge & usse 'q' m store kraenge

3. ab check krenge ki yadi p=0 & q=0 h means all values are in decreasing order toh just simply array ko reverse kr denge
aur return kr denge (function termination ke liye)

4. yadi p=0 & q=0 nhi h toh p-index-element & q-index-element ko swap kr denge (jisse curr. digit se greater value milegi)

5. but just bdi value ke liye p-index-element se aage se remaining subArray to reverse kra denge

6. finally hmme curr. digit se just bdi digit mil jayegi 
